The target is Aristotele Skotos, but because of him, whole city is in danger, threatened by five robots deprived of the Three Laws of Robotics. Only Jack O'Ryan, Skotos' son, sees the gravity of the situation and with the help of Nathan will thwart the plan. But he also thinks about revenge... against the father!

description: Kakeru has found his destiny at last: He has awesome telepathic powers, and his ability to control time makes him the most powerful psychic in the world. But when the girl he loves–the beautiful Ayano–is in danger, Kakeru may still be powerless to help, because Kakeru’s gift is also a curse: Every time he uses it, he creates a rift in the space-time continuum. Can he save Ayano without putting the entire universe at risk?
name: Time Rewind

description: Lobo joins the political fray, but where's the payday? Meanwhile, Garbage Man protects a little boy from a fellow experiment-gone-wrong. And Tanga's new friends don't appreciate her monster-fighting awesomeness as much as she'd like.
name: The Big (not so) Easy; The Moss is Always Greener;

description: Manny Grey is a telepath , but noone knows his secret . He meets Amanda, a lonely girl in search of love . The two become a pair . But Manny is a killer . he has already killed , and Nathan Never is on his trail . A thriller that is also a romance , told from three different perspectives : the one of the investigator , the one of the victim and the one of the murderer.
name: Gli occhi di uno sconosciuto

description: Hans Schneider , a "normal" boy,  is in love with Shara, who is a mutate. The awareness that they can not easily live together in a place like the City , drives him in a robbery with a gang of mutates.

description: Ikki is now one of the most famous Air Treck stars in the world, but not everyone believes in his talents: The Internet is buzzing with haters and critics, and Team Trident, Kansai’s leading Air Treck team, is burning to challenge him. Can Ikki prove he has what it takes to make it to the top?
name: Vol. 12

description: Child genius--and powerful wizard--Negi Springfield has had his share of magical adventures. But not even magic can help Negi with his latest challenge: acting with his students in the school play! It’s Cinderella, and with the adorable Negi playing Prince Charming, every girl in the school is vying for the lead role. Who will get to live happily ever after with Negi?
name: Once Upon a Time

description:
Some live in the deep darkness behind your eyelids. Some eat silence. Some thoughtlessly kill. Some simply drive men mad. Shortly after life emerged from the primordial ooze, these deadly creatures, mushi, came into terrifying being. And they still exist and wreak havoc in the world today. Ginko, a young man with a sardonic smile, has the knowledge and skill to save those plagued by mushi...perhaps.

Story Titles

  • The Green Gathering
  • The Soft Horns
  • The Pillow Path
  • The Light In the Eyelids
  • The Traveling Bog
name: They Have Existed Since the Dawn of Time

description:
Alter Ego asks 'Who's Afraid of Victor Fox?' with an examination of the Fox Comics of the 1940s - Blue Beetle, Phantom Lady, The Flame, et al..

Plus 'Superman vs. Wonder Man' starring Will Eisner, Jerry Iger, Sheldon Mayer, Jerry Siegel, and Harry Donenfeld!

Also, Part I of an interview with Jack Mendelsohn, artist/writer for MAD, Jacky's Diary, and much more!

Mushi, a terrifying primitive life-form, take countless shapes–most of them deadly to the human race. Enter Ginko, a mushi expert, known as a mushishi. Though his laconic smile and soft-spoken manner don’t seem imposing, he represents the human world’s greatest defense. When a fellow mushishi disappears, Ginko must search for him on a mushi-infested mountain, putting his own life on the line!

Story Titles

  • The Mountain Sleeps
  • The Sea of Brushstrokes
  • They That Breathe Ephemeral Life
  • Rain Comes and A Rainbow Is Born
  • The Veil Spore
name: Dark Mountain

description: They live on the shadowy border between the possible and the impossible–ancient life-forms known as mushi. Rare is the individual who can see them, but those with that special ability, the mushishi, can counter the creatures’ deadly effects on humans. After a young boy is orphaned in the forest, he is saved by a reclusive female mushishi. But the lake near the mushishi’s home holds a deadly secret, and the boy must find out what it is before his only friend is lost forever.
name: Vol. 3

description: Nebulous and unseen, existing in a state somewhere between life and death, mushi bring nothing but pain, suffering, and destruction to humans. A small community of wandering healers and naturalists known as mushishi protect humans from the ravages of these malevolent entities. Ginko, with his green eye and white hair, is a mushishi. But when Ginko tries to help a boy who seems to have found spring in the middle of winter, he and the boy both become victims of the life-sucking creatures.
name: Vol. 4

description: Imagine being blind–but that nebulous creatures called mushi allow you to see farther and better than any human, even into another person’s future. Ginko, whose lifelong task is to understand the many kinds of mushi, encounters such a woman and becomes entangled in the shocking future she sees for him.
name: Vol. 5

description: Ginko is sent on a fact-finding expedition to discover what the head of an ancient clan of mushishi is doing in an isolated, abandoned Japanese village. But the answer may be more than Ginko can handle: the Ragged Road he is investigating leads to mushi that can leave a man worse than dead!
name: Vol. 7

description: Ginko is a master of the ephemeral life form known as Mushi. Their influence can be as visible as a mountain never giving up its winter to allow for spring, or as subtle as a prank played in a child's game. To some they are a curse; to others they offer unimagined possibility. Read the final three volumes of Ginko's journeys in this one remarkable edition!
name: Vol. 8, 9 & 10
